I said "grow."

05:01.736 --> 05:05.261
It's like how we do book club,
but you never trust me

05:05.435 --> 05:06.697
to choose the book.

05:06.871 --> 05:08.830
That's because I know
some classics

05:09.004 --> 05:10.440
that maybe you
haven't heard of.

05:10.614 --> 05:12.399
Like The Da Vinci Code?
Guess what.

05:12.573 --> 05:16.533
I cracked the code.
It's Hardy Boysfor idiots!

05:16.707 --> 05:19.884
And you always second-guess
my aircraft carrier placement

05:20.058 --> 05:21.233
in Battleship.

05:23.540 --> 05:27.544
Those are the most important
pieces in the entire game.

05:27.718 --> 05:29.503
You cannot put them
on the perimeter.

05:29.677 --> 05:31.200
That is nautical suicide!

05:31.374 --> 05:32.897
So what?

05:33.071 --> 05:35.987
We play, I lose,
we play again!

05:36.161 --> 05:37.946
Why you gotta live so fast,
huh?

05:38.120 --> 05:39.426
[HUFFS]

05:39.600 --> 05:41.341
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

05:41.515 --> 05:43.604
[SIGHS]

05:43.778 --> 05:45.432
Look, I'm sorry, okay?

05:45.606 --> 05:47.347
It's just sometimes...

05:48.870 --> 05:50.567
You know the Olympic torch?

05:50.741 --> 05:51.960
Yeah.Yeah?

05:52.134 --> 05:53.614
Well, you're--
You're like that.

05:53.788 --> 05:55.659
Beautiful, amazing,
and really cool,

05:55.833 --> 05:58.923
and I've-- I've been given
the chance to hold you.

05:59.097 --> 06:01.143
But it just- It feels
like we're-- We're--

06:01.317 --> 06:03.624
We're running through
a massive storm,

06:03.798 --> 06:05.452
and there's all this air
just, like,

06:05.626 --> 06:07.802
gusting at you and-and--
And hitting your flame,

06:07.976 --> 06:11.240
and it's-it's super--
Super gusty out,

06:11.414 --> 06:12.981
and-and-and your flame,
it might g--

06:13.155 --> 06:14.417
It might get
blown out like--

06:14.591 --> 06:15.940
[EXHALES SHARPLY]
Because--

06:16.114 --> 06:18.508
Because of all the-the gusts
of-of air and--

06:18.682 --> 06:19.596
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

06:19.770 --> 06:20.728
You know what I mean?

06:20.902 --> 06:22.947
Not even a little bit.

06:23.121 --> 06:25.123
There's gotta be
a simpler way to say this.

06:28.213 --> 06:30.085
You're like a Zippo
in a tornado.

06:30.259 --> 06:32.566
I'm going for a walk.

06:32.740 --> 06:35.307
[♪♪♪]

06:35.482 --> 06:37.745
[EXHALES SHARPLY][GROANS]

06:46.101 --> 06:48.103
JOSH:
"I turned down sex
with Marilyn again.

06:48.277 --> 06:50.845
"I think, for some reason,
she sees that as a rejection.

06:51.019 --> 06:52.586
"Then we got into that whole,

06:52.760 --> 06:54.979
"'You're trying to fix me,'
conversation.

06:55.153 --> 06:58.461
"Man, if I could fix one thing, it'd be her bringing that up.

06:58.635 --> 07:00.376
"It's like we're
in this endless cycle.

07:00.550 --> 07:02.987
It's-- It's hard to remember
when we were happy."

07:04.859 --> 07:06.861
[♪♪♪]

07:07.035 --> 07:09.603
"So this is what love
feels like!"

07:12.170 --> 07:15.043
"Marilyn wants to have sex
all the time.

07:15.217 --> 07:17.349
"She says I'm good at it.

07:17.524 --> 07:20.048
[LAUGHS]
"She's also convinced
my abnormally sized penis

07:20.222 --> 07:21.789
"used to belong to
another man.

07:21.963 --> 07:23.965
[LAUGHS]
Ah, she's funny that way."

07:25.270 --> 07:27.055
[SIGHS]

07:32.234 --> 07:33.583
[SIGHS]

07:37.108 --> 07:39.546
TIGER:
Because virtually
everyone I knew died

07:39.720 --> 07:40.982
horribly
in front of my eyes,

07:41.156 --> 07:43.941
I view all love
as an attack,

07:44.115 --> 07:47.423
and I'm-- I'm really good
at fending off attacks.

07:47.597 --> 07:48.816
[BLEATS][TIGER LAUGHS]

07:48.990 --> 07:51.993
Oh, I just love
making you laugh.

07:52.167 --> 07:55.300
Hmm, but you-you've--
You've helped me realize

07:55.475 --> 07:57.259
that's an unhealthy
coping mechanism

07:57.433 --> 07:58.826
that I am committed
to changing.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.741
[BELL JANGLES]

08:02.133 --> 08:05.876
I-- So I mean,
I basically think

08:06.050 --> 08:07.922
we've covered everything.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.706
I mean, unless we have
more time.

08:09.880 --> 08:12.187
What am I talking about?
We have-- We have all the--

08:12.361 --> 08:14.319
All the time in the world.

08:14.494 --> 08:16.408
Oh, I had an epiphany earlier.

08:16.583 --> 08:19.847
I think crawling
through that pool of blood

08:20.021 --> 08:22.893
as a baby might be why
I don't like pools.

08:23.067 --> 08:25.766
Yeah, no, I know.

08:25.940 --> 08:27.855
I know, I know, I know.

08:28.029 --> 08:30.292
'Cause of the-- Yeah.
It was all, "Ah!"

08:30.466 --> 08:31.467
[BALL SMACKING]JOSH: No!

08:31.641 --> 08:32.468
[GRUNTS]

08:32.642 --> 08:34.470
[LAUGHS]

08:34.644 --> 08:37.691
Boom. Game, set, match
for the Linc-man.

08:37.865 --> 08:39.257
Yeah, yeah.

08:39.431 --> 08:41.608
You know, Lincs,
I was reading in my journal,

08:41.782 --> 08:43.305
and, God, we used to be
so happy.

08:43.479 --> 08:45.133
I'm not big
on proclamations,

08:45.307 --> 08:47.918
